glosses: To take a look at shortly, to glance over, to take a gander.

examples.text: Kitaba şöyle bir göz attım, pek bana göre değil.
examples.translation: I took a glance at the book, it's not quite for me.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish گوز آتمق (göz atmaḳ, “to cast one's eye on any thing, to conceive a desire for”), equivalent to compound of göz (“eye”) + atmak (“to throw”), literally “to throw (one's) eye”.
